{"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0,"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[]},"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":[],"metadata":{"id":"w_obMsY8gBHd"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["\n"],"metadata":{"id":"psmwpsj7gB1t"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# TP 4 : Mise en place d’un pipeline CI/CD avec GitHub Actions pour déployer une application Flask sur AWS EC2\n","\n","## 1. Objectifs pédagogiques\n","\n","À la fin de ce TP, l’étudiant sera capable de :\n","\n","* Comprendre le principe du CI/CD (Continuous Integration / Continuous Deployment)\n","* Utiliser GitHub Actions pour automatiser un déploiement\n","* Déployer une application web Flask sur une instance AWS EC2 Ubuntu\n","* Utiliser une clé SSH pour l’accès sécurisé à un serveur distant\n","* Adapter un déploiement selon un port attribué à un groupe\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 2. Contexte du TP\n","\n","Chaque groupe d’étudiants (groupe_1 à groupe_9) doit :\n","\n","* Créer un dépôt GitHub portant le **nom exact du groupe**\n","* Déployer automatiquement son application Flask sur une **instance EC2 Ubuntu partagée**\n","* Utiliser **un port spécifique** attribué au groupe\n","\n","### Attribution des ports\n","\n","| Groupe   | Port |\n","| -------- | ---- |\n","| groupe_1 | 5001 |\n","| groupe_2 | 5002 |\n","| groupe_3 | 5003 |\n","| ...      | ...  |\n","| groupe_9 | 5009 |\n","\n","Exemple :\n","\n","* Le dépôt `groupe_2` doit exposer l’application sur le port **5002**\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 3. Ressources mises à disposition\n","\n","* Adresse IP publique du serveur EC2\n","* Utilisateur : `ubuntu`\n","* Clé SSH privée : `assimi-key.pem`\n","* Python 3 déjà installé sur le serveur\n","\n","Les étudiants **n’ont pas à installer Python** sur le serveur.\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 4. Architecture cible\n","\n","```\n","Développeur (GitHub)\n","     |\n","     | git push\n","     v\n","GitHub Actions (CI/CD)\n","     |\n","     | SSH + SCP\n","     v\n","AWS EC2 Ubuntu\n","     |\n","     | Flask App\n","     v\n","Navigateur Web\n","```\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 5. Structure minimale du projet Flask\n","\n","Chaque dépôt doit respecter la structure suivante :\n","\n","```\n","<nom_du_groupe>/\n","├── app/\n","│   └── app.py\n","├── requirements.txt\n","├── run.py\n","└── .github/\n","    └── workflows/\n","        └── deploy.yml\n","```\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 6. Application Flask minimale\n","\n","Exemple de `app/app.py` :\n","\n","```python\n","from flask import Flask\n","\n","app = Flask(__name__)\n","\n","@app.route('/')\n","def index():\n","    return \"Hello from groupe_X\"\n","\n","if __name__ == '__main__':\n","    app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=500X)\n","```\n","\n","Chaque groupe doit remplacer `500X` par **son port attribué**.\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 7. Configuration des secrets GitHub\n","\n","Dans le dépôt GitHub :\n","\n","`Settings` → `Secrets and variables` → `Actions`\n","\n","Ajouter les secrets suivants :\n","\n","* `EC2_HOST` : IP publique du serveur\n","* `EC2_USER` : ubuntu\n","* `EC2_SSH_KEY` : contenu de la clé `assimi-key.pem`\n","* `APP_PORT` : port attribué au groupe\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 8. Workflow GitHub Actions (CI/CD)\n","\n","Créer le fichier `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` :\n","\n","```yaml\n","name: Deploy Flask App to EC2\n","\n","on:\n","  push:\n","    branches:\n","      - main\n","\n","jobs:\n","  deploy:\n","    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n","\n","    steps:\n","      - name: Checkout repository\n","        uses: actions/checkout@v4\n","\n","      - name: Setup SSH\n","        run: |\n","          mkdir -p ~/.ssh\n","          echo \"$EC2_SSH_KEY\" > ~/.ssh/id_rsa\n","          chmod 600 ~/.ssh/id_rsa\n","          ssh-keyscan -H $EC2_HOST >> ~/.ssh/known_hosts\n","        env:\n","          EC2_SSH_KEY: ${{ secrets.EC2_SSH_KEY }}\n","          EC2_HOST: ${{ secrets.EC2_HOST }}\n","\n","      - name: Copy project to EC2 (SCP)\n","        run: |\n","          scp -i ~/.ssh/id_rsa -r ./ $EC2_USER@$EC2_HOST:/home/ubuntu/${{ github.repository }}\n","        env:\n","          EC2_USER: ${{ secrets.EC2_USER }}\n","          EC2_HOST: ${{ secrets.EC2_HOST }}\n","\n","      - name: Install dependencies and run app\n","        run: |\n","          ssh $EC2_USER@$EC2_HOST << EOF\n","          cd /home/ubuntu/${{ github.repository }}\n","          python3 -m venv venv\n","          venv/bin/pip install -r requirements.txt\n","          nohup venv/bin/python run.py > app.log 2>&1 &\n","          EOF\n","        env:\n","          EC2_USER: ${{ secrets.EC2_USER }}\n","          EC2_HOST: ${{ secrets.EC2_HOST }}\n","```\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 9. Déclenchement du déploiement\n","\n","Le déploiement est automatiquement déclenché lorsque :\n","\n","* un `git push` est effectué sur la branche `main`\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 10. Vérification du déploiement\n","\n","Dans le navigateur, accéder à :\n","\n","```\n","http://IP_EC2:PORT_GROUPE\n","```\n","\n","Exemple pour groupe_2 :\n","\n","```\n","http://IP_EC2:5002\n","```\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 11. Consultation des logs sur le serveur\n","\n","```bash\n","cd /home/ubuntu/groupe_X\n","tail -f app.log\n","```\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 12. Travail demandé\n","\n","1. Créer le dépôt GitHub du groupe\n","2. Implémenter l’application Flask\n","3. Configurer les secrets GitHub Actions\n","4. Mettre en place le pipeline CI/CD\n","5. Vérifier l’accès à l’application via le navigateur\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 13. Livrables\n","\n","* Lien du dépôt GitHub\n","* Capture d’écran du workflow GitHub Actions réussi\n","* URL fonctionnelle de l’application déployée\n","\n","---\n","\n","Fin du TP\n"],"metadata":{"id":"aTQhWgjDuxKn"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":[],"metadata":{"id":"JqTXsmnPgJK8"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":[],"metadata":{"id":"xGTWMKdEgJux"}}]}